        <title>Session 1 Overview and Learning Objectives</title>
        <content>&lt;h3&gt;Overview and Learning Objectives&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Welcome to Session 1: Best Practices for Teaching Employability Skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In course #1, &lt;i&gt;Introduction to Workforce Preparation and Employability Skills&lt;/i&gt;, we identified and defined the Workforce Preparation Activities (WPA) that are delineated in the &lt;a href="$@GLOSSARYVIEWBYID*7399@$&amp;amp;mode=entry&amp;amp;hook=89" target="_blank"&gt;Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act (WIOA)&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;This course is designed to expand upon that introduction. This session will expose you to specific examples for incorporating employability skills into curriculum and instruction, so you can best meet the current needs of your adult learners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After completing this session, you will be able to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul type="disc"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-1: Explain the overlap in goals and objectives between college and career readiness instruction and general workforce preparation and employability skills. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-2: Define and demonstrate transferable skills. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-3: Describe ways teachers can help students connect learning objectives to their goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While referring to the Workforce Preparation Activities &amp;amp; Employability Skills checklist:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul type="disc"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-4: Identify examples of contextualized instructional activities in existing lessons/units that teach employability skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-5: Identify lessons and units you currently teach that would readily support the addition of workforce preparation and employability skills objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-6: Create a contextualized lesson or unit where workforce preparation activities and employability skills are fully integrated into the learning objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
